HEADWORD: Hinderling
<hw>Hind"er*ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hinderling</ets> one who comes behind his ancestors, fr. AS.
<ets>hinder</ets> behind. See <er>Hinder</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and cf.
<er>Hilding</er>.]</ety> <def>A worthless, base, degenerate person or
animal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Callander.</au></rj></p>

